"n. 近地点 【记】 peri(周围)＋gee(=ge o地)→周围之地→近 地点; 【同】 参考：apogee(远地点 ) n. 近地点(在月球或其它卫星绕地运行的椭圆轨道上靠近地球的点) 【记】peri靠近, gee = geo地球, 土地－近地点; 【参】apogee(n 远地点) 【记】peri- 近，周围 + gee；物理中g 代表地球引力，重力 【相关】apogee 远地点 perigee (n.)  ""point at which a celestial body is nearest the Earth,"" 1590s, from Modern Latin perigeum (15c.), from Late Greek peregeion, used by Ptolemy as a noun, properly neuter of adjective perigeios ""near the earth,"" from peri ges, from peri ""near"" (see peri-) + ges, genitive of ge ""earth""  (see Gaia)."
